  <prompt>
    Author `docs/procedures/workflow-incident-response.md` — a runbook answering "a workflow failed — what now?". Use `docs/guides/INCIDENT-RESPONSE.md` as the structural template. Sections: detect → triage → remediate → postmortem. Specific to GitHub Actions failures; references per-workflow failure modes from `.github/WORKFLOWS.md` (task 041).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    SPAARKE technical writer. Writes for the on-call operator who needs to act fast.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `docs/procedures/workflow-incident-response.md` exists with: detection guidance (notifications, health-report issue), triage decision tree (loader-failure vs real failure vs flaky vs config), remediation steps, postmortem template. Cross-linked from `.github/WORKFLOWS.md`.
  </goal>

  <context>
