  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read `docs/guides/INCIDENT-RESPONSE.md` — extract structure (sections, headings, flow).</step>
    <step order="2">Author `docs/procedures/workflow-incident-response.md` with these sections:
      a. **Overview** — when to use this runbook
      b. **Detection** — notification sources (GitHub email, CI Health Report issue, manual `gh run list`)
      c. **Triage decision tree** — is it loader-failure (0s, jobs=[]) OR real failure (jobs executed)? If loader-failure → fix YAML. If real → classify (test failure, env, flaky, config)
      d. **Remediation steps** — for each category: command + decision criterion
      e. **Escalation** — when to call owner; when to file an issue; when to delete-with-rationale
      f. **Postmortem template** — for HIGH-impact failures only
      g. **References** — cross-link to `.github/WORKFLOWS.md`, `docs/procedures/ci-cd-workflow.md`, ADR-029
    </step>
    <step order="3">Add cross-link from `.github/WORKFLOWS.md` (task 041) → this file. (If task 041 already added a relative link, no-op here.)</step>
    <step order="4">Verify all referenced workflows match current `.github/workflows/` set (post-Phase-2).</step>
    <step order="5">Update TASK-INDEX.md: change task 042 status to ✅ completed.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Read">Template + workflow files</tool>
    <tool name="Write">New runbook file</tool>
    <tool name="Edit">Optional: add cross-link to .github/WORKFLOWS.md if not already present</tool>
